            "text": "Some ways you can keep in contact with me:\n\n- Blog: https://t.co/Ak9LmctEvr\n- LinkedIn: https://t.co/LqHNED9n5n\n- Threads: https://t.co/UIiM6fHQCD\n- YouTube: https://t.co/QtNZ3TNmrr\n- Bluesky: https://t.co/WqV5B8UHAJ",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1909485125206696279"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1909336659260219845",
            "text": "[BLOGGED] DB Connection Strings in Deployed Azure Functions\n\nRead more here:\n\nhttps://t.co/y9D05zPwtr",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1909336659260219845"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1909293618545799636",
            "text": "[ANNOUNCEMENT] Journal and Mood Tracking Micro-SaaS Released ! https://t.co/dJl7fz6ui4\n\nRead more here:\nhttps://t.co/y4d6vUALHQ",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1909293618545799636"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1909217872842289513",
            "text": "[BLOGGED] How To: Creating a Private Journal and Mood Tracking App Using .NET 6, Chat GPT, C# and Visual Studio 2022\n\nRead here:\n\nhttps://t.co/rNKv28A3JJ",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1909217872842289513"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1909122725903220759",
            "text": "[BLOGGED] Improving Productivity Using the 3 M’s!\n\nRead more here:\n\nhttps://t.co/2rAiEfo5Ra",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1909122725903220759"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1909003082517610678",
            "text": "RT @AngryEda: Perpetual motion machines",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1909003082517610678"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908894000213340202",
            "text": "💀💀😅 so any AI checker that has been trained on figures of speech will detect every use of a figure of speech as \"written by AI\". Okay o https://t.co/5h9Pchth1c",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908894000213340202"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908817587363893262",
            "text": "Mind you, this wasn't even nearly my best work. It was past 12 midnight. I'd been up all day designing and researching; my fingers were hurting and I was sleepy. But yeah, AI wrote 38% of the thing for me 😂 The world is truly going to shit at this point",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908817587363893262"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908817583999959061",
            "text": "If anybody is passing your written work through AI checkers, I'm so sorry 💀\n\nI just pasted my own work in an AI checker and it flagged a sentence. The sentence in question mentioned \"memorabilia\" so it must've been written by AI 😂😂\n\nAnother AI checker flagged my work as 38% AI https://t.co/bZL5rajkqx https://t.co/7o5HnTtHEu",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908817583999959061"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908774689956114455",
            "text": "Completed v1 of an end-to-end AI solution for a client project.\n\nFeatures:\n\n -content ingestion, parsing and vectorisation\n -web portal and document search\n -RAG agent and pipeline\n\nBuilt with https://t.co/KDFiYvYeHr, C#, Elasticsearch Semantic Kernel and running in Azure. Having",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908774689956114455"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908732716645794227",
            "text": "Hmm....looks Australia is getting another relic from space to showcase in their museums! 😆\n\nJokes aside, its nice to see ISRO, handling the issue of space debris in such a responsible manner. I assumed portions of the delivery medium often floated around in space for some time. https://t.co/NiGyQzkL1l",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908732716645794227"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908731528122691778",
            "text": "RT @pyconindia: The Call for Proposals is LIVE for #PyConIndia2025\nGot something exciting to share with the Python community?\nYou can submi…",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908731528122691778"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908658277636083927",
            "text": "I am experimenting with a new airdrop flow to encourage Farcaster engagement. Based Bits users with a 7+ day streak will receive a DM from me with a link to claim 50 BBITS. The link expires after 7 days, so don’t sleep on it :) https://t.co/EaAZuSxYcL",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908658277636083927"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908653568120545519",
            "text": "If you have a 7-day streak on Based Bits and you’re on Farcaster, you should have received a message from me with a little something. Check your DMs!",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908653568120545519"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908528742575599706",
            "text": "Proved my point that they do not use the software that they make. The WaveShell wrapper is the only way to load Waves plugins on a Mac. On Windows, you have to do a long workaround to get the individual Waves plugins to show up. But you get WaveShell by default https://t.co/n21uGwZpzi",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908528742575599706"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908524683592343909",
            "text": "RT @ImadeIyamu: Small acts of rudeness irritate me. An unnecessary lie, a demanding/entitled vibe, a mean joke at someone in need. I can't…",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908524683592343909"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908495615853494558",
            "text": "RT @BoredLilith: If you can, please offer your delivery person some cold water. It’s scorching outside, and some riders even arrive visibly…",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908495615853494558"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908494217753526305",
            "text": "Kapow 💥 https://t.co/6wPTY83ieP",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908494217753526305"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908463136836919529",
            "text": "Cursor's usage-based pricing for Sonnet Max isn't just 5 cents per request. It's a total of the base price of the monthly $20 subscription + the $0.05 PAYG price. Would be nice to be able to skip the subscription entirely and only do the PAYG. Or even have a lower PAYG base price",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908463136836919529"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908443211095294162",
            "text": "[NEW COURSE COMING SOON]\n\nI have partnered with top training platform @Pluralsight to bring you a new AI course.\n\n - ChatGPT Pro, OpenAI o3-mini\n\nMore details:\nhttps://t.co/1TlD7sNT0R https://t.co/7CqftYCiIM",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908443211095294162"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908429895631352222",
            "text": "So much cool stuff being shipped from @Microsoft.",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
                "1908429895631352222"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "1908249501178970583",
            "text": "[BLOGGED] Useful Azure Open AI, Prompt Engineering, and Large Language Model (LLM) Resources for Developer\n\nRead:\n\nhttps://t.co/sANONhzFZe",
            "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
